Here's how you could refactor the `Test` method:

```csharp
public class Animal
{
    private int _myProtectedField = 2;

    public virtual void Test()
    {
        Debug.Assert(this == typeof(Animal), "This should only be called on an instance of Animal.");
        Console.WriteLine("Test: " + _myProtectedField);
    }
}

public class Cat : Animal
{
    public override void Test()
    {
        base.Test(); // Call the overridden method if needed.
        Debug.Assert(this == typeof(Cat), "This should only be called on an instance of Cat.");
        Console.WriteLine("Test: Protected field accessed.");
    }
}
```

